HEADWORD: Sleeping
<hw>Sleep"ing</hw>, <def><pos>a. & n.</pos> from
<er>Sleep</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sleeping car</b></col>, <cd>a railway car or carrriage,
arranged with apartments and berths for sleeping.</cd> --
<col><b>Sleeping partner</b></col> <fld>(Com.)</fld>, <cd>a dormant
partner. See under <er>Dormant</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Sleeping
table</b></col> <fld>(Mining)</fld>, <cd>a stationary inclined platform
on which pulverized ore is washed; a kind of buddle.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sleepish</ent>⟦br⟧
